    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1896</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Jan. 20.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 145.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The principal, if not the only, event of
                    importance during the past two months was the release on parole of the remaining
                    political prisoners, which occurred on the 1st instant.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert S. Willis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
